ts()`\n- **Endpoint**: N/A (Instance method)\n\n#### `enable_prompts_with(prompts: PromptsCapability)`\n- **Description**: Enables prompts capabilities with a specific configuration.\n- **Method**: `self.enable_prompts_with(prompts)`\n- **Endpoint**: N/A (Instance method)\n\n#### `enable_resources()`\n- **Description**: Enables resources capabilities.\n- **Method**: `self.enable_resources()`\n- **Endpoint**: N/A (Instance method)\n\n#### `enable_resources_with(resources: ResourcesCapability)`\n- **Description**: Enables resources capabilities with a specific configuration.\n- **Method**: `self.enable_resources_with(resources)`\n- **Endpoint**: N/A (Instance method)\n\n#### `enable_tools()`\n- **Description**: Enables tools capabilities.\n- **Method**: `self.enable_tools()`\n- **Endpoint**: N/A (Instance method)\n\n#### `enable_tools_with(tools: ToolsCapability)`\n- **Description**: Enables tools capabilities with a specific configuration.\n- **Method**: `self.enable_tools_with(tools)`\n- **Endpoint**: N/A (Instance method)\n\n#### `enable_tool_list_changed()`\n- **Description**: Indicates that the tool list has changed.\n- **Method**: `self.enable_tool_list_changed()`\n- **Endpoint**: N/A (Instance method)\n\n### Example Usage (Conceptual)\n```rust\nlet capabilities = ServerCapabilitiesBuilder::new()\n    .enable_logging()\n    .enable_completions_with(json!({}))\n    .build();\n```\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### ServerCapabilitiesBuilder: Enable Tools (Rust)\n\nSource: https://docs.rs/rmcp/latest/rmcp/model/struct.ServerCapabilitiesBuilder_search=Option%3CT%3E%2C+%28T+-%3E+U%29+-%3E+Option%3CU%3E\n\nEnables tool usage capabilities for the ServerCapabilitiesBuilder. This method is part of the chainable builder pattern.\n\n```rust\npub fn enable_tools( self, ) -> ServerCapabilitiesBuilder<ServerCapabilitiesBuilderState<EXPERIMENTAL, LOGGING, COMPLETIONS, PROMPTS, RESOURCES, true>>\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Attribute Macro: tool_handler\n\nSource: https://docs.rs/rmcp/latest/rmcp/attr.tool_handler_search=\n\nThis macro generates the handler for `tool_call` and `list_tools` methods within an implementation block, utilizing an existing `ToolRouter` instance. It is available when the `macros` and `server` crate features are enabled.\n\n```APIDOC\n## Attribute Macro: tool_handler\n\n### Description\nThis macro will generate the handler for `tool_call` and `list_tools` methods in the implementation block, by using an existing `ToolRouter` instance.\n\nAvailable on **crate features`macros` and `server`** only.\n\n### Parameters\n#### Path Parameters\nNone\n\n#### Query Parameters\nNone\n\n#### Request Body\nNone\n\n### Method\nAttribute Macro\n\n### Endpoint\nN/A\n\n### Parameters\n#### Path Parameters\nNone\n\n#### Query Parameters\nNone\n\n#### Request Body\nNone\n\n### Usage\n- `router` (Expr): The expression to access the `ToolRouter` instance. Defaults to `self.tool_router`.\n\n### Request Example\n```rust\n#[tool_handler]\nimpl ServerHandler for MyToolHandler {\n    // ...implement other handler\n}\n\n// Or using a custom router expression:\n#[tool_handler(router = self.get_router().await)]\nimpl ServerHandler for MyToolHandler {\n   // ...implement other handler\n}\n```\n\n### Response\n#### Success Response (200)\nN/A (macro expansion generates methods that return results)\n\n#### Response Example\n```rust\n// Expanded code for demonstration:\nimpl ServerHandler for MyToolHandler {\n       async fn call_tool(\n        &self,\n        request: CallToolRequestParam,\n        context: RequestContext<RoleServer>,\n    ) -> Result<CallToolResult, rmcp::ErrorData> {\n        let tcc = ToolCallContext::new(self, request, context);\n        self.tool_router.call(tcc).await\n    }\n\n    async fn list_tools(\n        &self,\n        _request: Option<PaginatedRequestParam>,\n        _context: RequestContext<RoleServer>,\n    ) -> Result<ListToolsResult, rmcp::ErrorData> {\n        let items = self.tool_router.list_all();\n        Ok(ListToolsResult::with_all_items(items))\n    }\n}\n```\n```\n\n--------------------------------\n\n### Rust Attribute Macro: tool_handler\n\nSource: https://docs.rs/rmcp/latest/rmcp/attr.tool_handler_search=u32+-%3E+bool\n\nThe `tool_handler` attribute macro automatically generates handler functions for `tool_call` and `list_tools` methods. It requires a `ToolRouter` instance, which can be accessed via a provided expression or defaults to `self.tool_router`. This macro is available when the `macros` and `server` crate features are enabled.\n\n```rust\n#[tool_handler]\nimpl ServerHandler for MyToolHandler {\n    // ...implement other handler\n}\n```\n\n```rust\n#[tool_handler(router = self.get_router().await)]\nimpl ServerHandler for MyToolHandler {\n   // ...implement other handler\n}\n```\n\n```rust\nimpl ServerHandler for MyToolHandler {\n       async fn call_tool(\n        &self,\n        request: CallToolRequestParam,\n        context: RequestContext<RoleServer>,\n    ) -> Result<CallToolResult, rmcp::ErrorData> {\n        let tcc = ToolCallContext::new(self, request, context);\n        self.tool_router.call(tcc).await\n    }\n\n    async fn list_tools(\n        &self,\n        _request: Option<PaginatedRequestParam>,\n        _context: RequestContext<RoleServer>,\n    ) -> Result<ListToolsResult, rmcp::ErrorData> {\n        let items = self.tool_router.list_all();\n        Ok(ListToolsResult::with_all_items(items))\n    }\n}\n```","toolTelemetry":{},"contents":[{"type":"text","text":"### ServerCapabilities Struct\n\nSource: https://docs.rs/rmcp/latest/rmcp/model/struct.ServerCapabilities_search=Option%3CT%3E%2C+%28T+-%3E+U%29+-%3E+Option%3CU%3E\n\nDefines the capabilities that a server can expose, including experimental features, logging, completions, prompts, resources, and tools.\n\n```APIDOC\n## Struct ServerCapabilities\n\n### Description\nRepresents the server's capabilities, outlining features like logging, completions,