{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"490940a5-2c2d-4992-b754-798600de609e","content":"Found it. The shim returns `\"capabilities\":{}` — **no tools advertised**. In rmcp 1.1, you must explicitly declare capabilities. The `ShimHandler` doesn't override the `capabilities()` method, so it defaults to empty. Let me check the exact trait method:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_0144h5GoH58etLJibiTBw9Me","name":"context7-query-docs","arguments":{"libraryId":"/websites/rs_rmcp_rmcp","query":"ServerHandler trait required methods get_info capabilities serve_server how to declare tool capabilities"},"type":"function","toolTitle":"Query Documentation","intentionSummary":"ServerHandler trait required methods get_info capabilities serve_server how to declare tool capabilities"}],"interactionId":"f697c919-00bd-42ba-9c55-f9115fcb6a90","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the issue. In rmcp 1.1, `serve_server` uses the `ServerHandler` trait to determine capabilities. The handler needs to declare capabilities explicitly. Looking at the test output:\n\n```json\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":{\"protocolVersion\":\"2024-11-05\",\"capabilities\":{},\"serverInfo\":{\"name\":\"engram-shim\",\"version\":\"0.0.1\"}}}\n```\n\nThe `capabilities` is empty `{}`, meaning tools are NOT advertised. This likely causes Copilot CLI to consider the server as having no tools, and potentially disconnect or ignore it.\n\n\nThe `ServerHandler` trait has a default `capabilities()` method that returns empty capabilities, and since `ShimHandler` doesn't override it, I need to implement that method to explicitly declare the tools capability.\n\nChecking the rmcp source...","outputTokens":481},"id":"645bdf59-8a96-4a9d-a52f-98c7e5a1636f","timestamp":"2026-03-20T19:41:32.137Z","parentId":"93d2e667-0137-4a4b-8912-400c5ec6af65"}
